## Base Rules

- Prefer public framework packages under `github.com/cybersaksham/gogo`.
- Never import `github.com/cybersaksham/gogo/internal` from this project.
- When using a Gogo feature, first check `.agent/rules/gogo/package-feature-index.md`
  for the owning package and then inspect public symbols with `go doc`.
- Keep first-party apps under `apps/`; keep project wiring under `{{.ProjectName}}/`.
- Keep generated structure app-based: each app owns models, migrations, admin
  registrations, API views, forms, templates, static assets, tasks, services,
  permissions, and tests.
- Keep environment values in `.env`; commit `.env.example` only.
- Treat `GOGO_SECRET_KEY`, database URLs, broker credentials, email credentials,
  session data, tokens, uploads, and local database files as sensitive.
- Update tests and docs when changing public behavior, settings, commands,
  generated files, migration behavior, auth/session behavior, APIs, admin
  behavior, or queue behavior.
- Run focused checks first, then broaden based on risk.

## Common Commands

Inside this project, run project-aware commands through `manage.go` so Gogo can
load the generated project settings, router, admin registry, app configs, and
queue tasks. Use the installed `gogo` binary for `startproject` and global
version/help checks.

```bash
make test
make check
make run
make tidy
gogo help
gogo version
go run manage.go help
go run manage.go version
go run manage.go check
go run manage.go check --deploy
```

Use `go run manage.go check --deploy` before production deployment.

The full CLI command list is in `.agent/rules/gogo/package-feature-index.md`.
